ActEconomic Action Plan 2014 Act, No. 1
Budget Implementation Act, 2017, No. 1
SubjectOrder Fixing the Coming into Force of Certain Provisions of (1) the Economic Action Plan 2014 Act, No. 1 on June 1, 2020; and (2) the Budget Implementation Act, 2017, No. 1 on June 1, 2021
PrecisOrder Fixing (1) June 1, 2020 as the day on which subsection 256(2), sections 257 and 261, subsection 262(3), sections 263 to 266, 293, and 296 of the Proceeds of Crime (Money Laundering) and Terrorist Financing Act (the Act), pursuant to subsection 298(3) of the Economic Action Plan 2014 Act, No. 1, chapter 20 of the Statutes of Canada 2014, COME INTO FORCE; and (2) June 1, 2021 as the day on which subsections 408(1) and 415(2) and (3), section 417, subsections 423(1) and (3) and sections 425 and 438 of this Act, pursuant to subsection 441(1) of the Budget Implementation Act, 2017, No. 1, chapter 20 of the Statutes of Canada, 2017, COME INTO FORCE.
